com.ibm.team.interop.common

Interface IValueMapping


  • public interface IValueMapping
    Class to represent an enumerated value mapping for a synchronized property. Each value mapping identifies a possible value for an external object property, the corresponding Jazz property value, and whether this is the default value for a multi-valued mapping in either direction.

    Multi-valued mappings are represented by creating more than one IValueMapping object with the same external or Jazz item property value. When a source value has multiple possible target values, if the target object property already has one of the possible target values, it is unchanged. Otherwise, one of the possible targets must be designated the default value, or an error will occur.

    If a source value is null or the empty string, then it will be used as the mapping if the state being mapped includes no value at all for the source property (as well as if the value is null or the empty string).

    Since:
    0.5
